snippet.textDisplay:
I’m trying to put this as delicately as possible.

Any loss of life to suicide is tragic. The pain an individual must be suffering to get to that point must be unimaginable.

However, the stress caused by CPS was only possible because she attacked her partner.

I cannot claim to know what caused her to do such a thing. Nor can I know if the abuse was a two way street, but when you attack someone, you go through legal action against you. You lose your job because that organisation does not like the stigma of having a domestic abuser on their payroll.

Had the genders been flipped, we would all be saying something different. We’d be making Netflix documentaries on the abusive male and what he did in life.

Regardless, I hope she finds the peace she could not find whilst alive and my thoughts do go out to her family. The loss of a loved one is one of the worst pains imaginable.
